<!--
  Introductory text

  This text is expected to explain what a community is, and also how to
  submit a proposal for consideration under the community approval process.
-->

<h2>OpenSolaris Communities</h2>

<p>
OpenSolaris communities are social groups whose members engage in open
conversations and will have representation in the governance process.
Although communities do not have source repositories, it's expected that
communities will endorse technical <a href="/os/projects/">projects</a> and have projects of their
own.
</p>

<p>
Community members can propose new communities by writing to the
<code>opensolaris-discuss</code> list outlining items such as goals,
technical scope, potential participants, leaders, and activities.
Proposals need to remain on the list for at least one week, and
applicants are expected to engage the community in conversation and
update their proposals based on feedback. Additionally, proposals need
one vote of approval from a CAB member. If community consensus is
reached, the community will be opened.  If no consensus is reached or if
a CAB vote is not secured, the proposal will be considered void after 30
days.
</p>

<!--
  Community listing follows.
-->
<a name="all"></a>



    
        
        <dl>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/edu/">Academic and Research</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    A community for students, faculty, and researchers
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/appliances/">Appliances</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    A community for building diverse appliances using OpenSolaris
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/approachability/">Approachability</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    The Approachability community will be focused on eliminating annoying and substantial gaps in the Solaris operating system. 
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/arc/">Architecture Process and Tools</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    System Architecture Process and Tools
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/brandz/">BrandZ</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    BrandZ (Branded Zones) extends the Solaris Zones infrastructure to enable the creation of non-native zones on a Solaris system, including Linux Zones.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/chinese_users/">Chinese Users</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    A Community targetting to the Chinese market, with Chinese Universities as the top priority.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/cab/">Community Advisory Board (CAB)</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    The OpenSolaris Community Advisory Board (CAB) is focused on developing a governance proposal, driving consensus within the community, and serving as a link between Sun and non-Sun participants. 
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/dtrace/">DTrace</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    DTrace is a comprehensive dynamic tracing framework for the Solaris Operating Environment.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/databases/">Databases</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    This community is a gathering place for both database users and engineers building databases on Solaris.  Any discussions relevant to databases on Solaris are welcome here.  Some potential discussion topics: how to improve Solaris to better serve database technologies; how to make databases run best on Solaris; differences between various database technologies and which one is best suited for a given use; and so on.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/desktop/">Desktop</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    The OpenSolaris Desktop Community
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/device_drivers/">Device Drivers</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    The Device Drivers will promote and support the creation of additional device drivers for OpenSolaris.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/documentation/">Documentation</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    Documentation, including the feature documentation collections, man pages, and guides.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/fm/">Fault Management</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    Tools, technology, infrastructure, and content to permit Solaris and Sun products to recover from, diagnose, isolate, and explain faults.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/gnu_solaris/">GNU Solaris</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    A community about GNU Solaris
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/games/">Games on OpenSolaris</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    The OpenSolaris games community serves to list games that can be played on OpenSolaris, to provide instructions for downloading and running them, and to host new games that OpenSolaris contributors have written.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/hpcdev/">HPC Developer</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    The goal of this community is to promote High Performance Computing on OpenSolaris.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/immigrants/">Immigrants</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    Bridging the gap and easing the transition between other UNIX OS's and OpenSolaris
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/install/">Installation and Packaging</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    Technologies and processes related to installation, packaging, patching, and construction of OpenSolaris distributions. 
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/int_localization/">Internationalization and Localization</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    Community for OpenSolaris software internationalization and localization. 
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/laptop/">Laptop</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    Using Solaris as your ultimate mobile computing platform.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/marketing/">Marketing</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    The Marketing Community is here to help to build and support the OpenSolaris community.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/mdb/">Modular Debugger (MDB)</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    Solaris Modular Debugger (MDB) is a debugger designed to facilitate analysis of certain problems.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/nfs/">NFS</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    Network File System as implemented in OpenSolaris
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/networking/">Networking</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    A community on Networking
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/on/">Nevada Development</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    Information for Nevada ON developers
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/observability/">Observability</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    Tools and facilities for observing software and hardware behavior on OpenSolaris.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/printing/">OpenSolaris Printing</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    Printing technologies
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/performance/">Performance</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    The OpenSolaris Performance Community
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/power_pc/">PowerPC</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    The goal of this community is to create an OpenSolaris port that runs on PowerPC hardware.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/security/">Security</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    The Security Geek Corner
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/smf/">Service Management Facility (smf(5))</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    The Service Management Facility is a mechanism to define, deliver and manage long-running application services for Solaris.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/volume_manager/">Solaris Volume Manager</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    An enterprise class logical volume manager. The goal of this community is to discuss its features and collaborate on future enhancements.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/storage/">Storage</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    A community for the drivers, libraries and utilities enabling networked storage transports
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/sysadmin/">Systems Administrators</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    A community for systems administrators, engineers, and architects to collaborate and enhance the manageability of OpenSolaris.

                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/testing/">Testing</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    Community for software testing discussions and collaboration.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/tools/">Tools</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    The Tools community covers compilers, source code management, and tools used in software construction in OpenSolaris generally.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/ufs/">Unix File Systems (UFS)</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    General Discussion about the Unix File System(UFS), the generic file system layer and file system utilities technologies
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/os_user_groups/">User Groups</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    A community of OpenSolaris user groups.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/x_win/">X Window System</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    The X Window System as implemented in OpenSolaris.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/xen/">Xen</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    The Xen community is intended to focus specifically on the
OpenSolaris side of the OpenSolaris on Xen project.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/zfs/">ZFS</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    ZFS is a new kind of filesystem that provides simple administration, transactional semantics, end-to-end data integrity, and immense scalability.
                </dd>
            
                <dt>
                    <a href="/os/community/zones/">Zones</a>
                </dt>
                <dd>
                    Zones provide a means of creating virtualized operating system environments within an instance of Solaris, allowing one or more processes to run in isolation from other activity on the system.
                </dd>
            
        </dl>
                        
                    </div>
